# Enterprise Private Deployment Configuration

# Single-tenant mode configuration
# Set this to enable single-tenant (private deployment) mode

# Option 1: Using environment variables
ENTERPRISE_ID=69b69cd7331f0d2ee69f9676
ENTERPRISE_MODE=single-tenant

# Option 2: Using config file
# Create config/enterprise.json with:
# {
#   "enterpriseId": "your-enterprise-id",
#   "mode": "single-tenant",
#   "allowPublicResources": false,
#   "customDomain": "your-domain.com"
# }

# Configuration options:
# - ENTERPRISE_ID: The MongoDB ObjectId of your enterprise
# - ENTERPRISE_MODE: "single-tenant" or "multi-tenant" (default)
# - ALLOW_PUBLIC_RESOURCES: Whether to allow public resources in single-tenant mode

# When in single-tenant mode:
# - All API requests are automatically scoped to the configured enterprise
# - Public resource visibility is controlled by ALLOW_PUBLIC_RESOURCES
# - Login page automatically uses the enterprise's OAuth configuration
# - Admin users are determined by the enterprise's owner and members
